rComments: Might look like a tough teacher but he's actually really nice. Exams are fair with a little trickery. TA's suck.
Interesting content but made boring by prof. Not exactly the most enthusiastic of profs. Midterm was harder than expected. Easy labs  easy marks

Honestly, I loved the way he taught the class. His exam questions can be tricky but focusing more on the lecture keeps you set! He's really caring and passionate about what he's teaching so I never got bored! :)  Wish I had him again this semester!

amazing prof (some people find him boring but I genuinely enjoyed his lectures) labs are 40% and usually a mark booster (depending on ur work and ur ta) he liked making questions tricky which can be frustrating very lecture heavy, the mid term for 2016 was literally anything and everything he said

rComments: Wouldnt recommend if you have weaknesses in chemistry and math; its an entry level course with no prerequisites so that confuses me. Prof has not designed the course for students to do well in terms of resources to help students study. Lectures can sometimes be biased towards his interests. He could learn from Prof Sicchia in terms of course design

rComments: I really enjoyed the course with Professor Mitchell. He is very lecture/slides based, and likes to include a few tricky questions for those who pay attention. The tutorial assignments weren't a breeze but they are manageable. Overall, I would definitely recommend it to those interested in the science field and are intrigued to learn more.
The course itself is great, the prof did not do it justice.

Great prof that has a casual style of teaching which really makes it interesting to attend class. Assignments take some work but are good mark boosters. Everything is lec/tut based. You get to make a cheat sheet for equations which is nice and midterm/exam is fully lecture based. Pay attention during class and tutorials and you will do well.
4 assignments - 2 hard & 2 ok take up lots of time though! Class is great, tutorials are very helpful especially the ones that are NOT mandatory :)
Fairly easy class if you are ok with doing some math. There are a few equations to memorize but you get a cheat sheet to help. His exams are completely lecture based (right from the lecture slides)

Don't take this course if you don't have to! Lots of stuff to read and the lectures are long and boring. Course if broken down into quizes/midterm/final. Quizzes are worth 30% and they are not easy. If you take this course know ur textbook and tutorial material rlly well.

Very great teacher, knowledgeable very easy to understand but exams definitely on the tricky side. Learn a lot from him more than my other environmental sci courses. He is very updated about envio issues, feel free to ask him anything. Not an easy course overall for people take this as an elective.
